title: House Of Representatives | Fox News
description: Stay connected with the latest House of Representatives news and highlights from around the world with Fox News House of Representatives. Get up-to-the-minute coverage, expert analysis, and thrilling updates on all things regarding the House of Representatives.

Bipartisan lawmakers target federal HOME program to cut housing costs for middle-income Americans, shifting infrastructure expenses from developers to cities.

Rep. Jasmine Crockett, D-Texas, named Lee Zeldin as among figures who accepted money from "somebody" by the name of Jeffrey Epstein. Zeldin said that Epstein was not the late disgraced financier by the same name. (Credit: CSPAN)
Thomas Windom, fired federal prosecutor from Jack Smith's team, faces criminal referral from Rep. Jim Jordan for refusing to answer congressional questions.
Texas appeals federal court ruling that blocked new redistricting map, potentially costing Republicans five House seats in upcoming midterm elections.

The House failed to censure Del. Stacey Plaskett, D-V.I., for texting convicted pedophile Jeffrey Epstein. Rep. Ralph Norman criticizes Plaskett's defense and discusses Rep. James Comer's subpoena of Epstein's bank records and flight logs.
Trump-backed MAGA Inc. launches major ad campaign for Matt Van Epps in Tennessee special election against Democrat Aftyn Behn for crucial House seat
Rep. Jamie Raskin, D-Md., was ridiculed for his defense of colleague Stacey Plaskett, who Republicans sought to censure Tuesday for texting Jeffrey Epstein during a 2019 hearing about Donald Trump.
The House voted to not censure Del. Stacey Plaskett over Jeffrey Epstein text messages, with three Republicans joining Democrats to vote "no."

Rep. Jamie Raskin, D-Md., said that U.S. Virgin Islands Congressional Delegate Stacey Plaskett was simply 'taking a phone call from her constituent' when she was texting Jeffrey Epstein during a 2019 Trump hearing. (Credit: US House Pool)
Former New York State Sen. David Carlucci and former New York City councilman Joe Borelli discuss the Democratic Party's leadership, message and direction on 'America Reports.'
Rep. Tim Burchett, R-Tenn., unpacks Democrats' 'double standard' about the Epstein files after they became one step closer to being released on 'The Ingraham Angle.'
President Trump called for unified federal AI standards, as House Republicans signal their support for blocking state rules and protections.
Rep. Anna Paulina Luna, R-Fla., discusses the Epstein files and why she believes the disgraced financier may have been connected to foreign intelligence on 'The Will Cain Show.'

Fox News host Will Cain recaps President Donald Trump’s reception of Saudi Arabia’s Crown Prince Mohammed bin Salman and gives his take on the House of Representatives voting to release the Epstein files on ‘The Will Cain Show.’
House Speaker Mike Johnson speaks ahead of the Epstein files vote and criticizes the legislation as 'flawed.'
House Democrats split as some defy leadership to rebuke Rep. Jesús "Chuy" García over controversial election timing that critics say undermined fair process.
House overwhelmingly votes to force DOJ release of Jeffrey Epstein files in bipartisan push led by Reps. Massie and Khanna, despite GOP leadership concerns.
Reps. Ro Khanna, D-Calif., Thomas Massie, R-Ky., and Marjorie Taylor Greene, R-Ga., demand the Senate pass a bill to release all Jeffrey Epstein files.
Rep. Ro Khanna, D-Calif., Rep. Thomas Massie, R-Ky., and Rep. Marjorie Taylor Greene, R-Ga., speak ahead of the upcoming House vote on a bill to compel the release of more Jeffrey Epstein files.
Speaker Johnson revealed his decision on the House's forthcoming vote on forcing the release of the files on Jeffrey Epstein.
‘Special Report’ anchor Bret Baier discusses the upcoming House vote to release the Jeffrey Epstein files on ‘America’s Newsroom.’
House Freedom Caucus rallies behind Rep. Brandon Gill's push to impeach Judge James Boasberg over his role in subpoenas targeting Republican lawmakers.
President Donald Trump says he would sign legislation forcing the Justice Department to release all Jeffrey Epstein files as the House prepares to vote.
President Donald Trump speaks about legislation that would force the Justice Department to release all of its files on the Jeffrey Epstein case.
Rep. Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez distanced herself from New York City Council member Chi Osse's effort to primary House Democratic Leader Hakeem Jeffries.
House Republicans express cautious support for bipartisan bill requiring DOJ to release Jeffrey Epstein files after President Donald Trump endorsed the measure Sunday.

‘Ruthless’ podcast co-hosts Michael Duncan and John Ashbrook discuss the state of leadership in the Democratic party and Michelle Obama remarking that the U.S. is not ready for a woman president on ‘The Story.’
Rep. Jamie Raskin suggests Democratic Party could welcome Rep. Marjorie Taylor Greene, drawing boos from the Miami fundraiser crowd as he promotes a "big tent" approach.
Far-left Gen Z activist Chi Ossé filed paperwork against House Minority Leader Hakeem Jeffries, D-N.Y., marking a generational split within Democratic Party.
High-stakes redistricting battle unfolds as Trump pressures Indiana lawmakers to redraw congressional maps ahead of 2026 midterms for House control.
